r5404 | felicity | 2003-06-06 14:01:32 -0700 (Fri, 06 Jun 2003) | 4 lines

bug 2030: if a message doesn't have a message-id header, then
'spamassassin -r' would learn it as ham instead of spam.  adds a
'scalar()' to the call so that a lack of message-id will be ok.

