r4909 | felicity | 2003-03-29 08:45:13 -0800 (Sat, 29 Mar 2003) | 4 lines

We check to see if it's a magic token, then modify the token to strip
off some non-alphanum chars.  This means that "**NSPAM" would still
get through.

