------------------------------------------------------------------------
r4899 | felicity | 2003-03-28 12:15:17 -0800 (Fri, 28 Mar 2003) | 5 lines

Bug 1699: The code wasn't protecting the Bayes DB "magic" tokens (tracks
num ham/spam, etc.) from being overwritten if they occured in a message.
This allows mails to corrupt the DB either maliciously or if they discuss
the tokens.

