new rule for test

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r4869 | felicity | 2003-03-27 09:54:21 -0800 (Thu, 27 Mar 2003) | 5 lines

bug 1514: spamd was trying to use "../lib" which is ok most of the time,
but during a "make test" on perl 5.005 it errored out with the "bytes.pm"
error.  so we now check for a "../blib/lib" first and use it if it exists.
otherwise, we continue with "../lib".

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r4867 | felicity | 2003-03-27 09:48:10 -0800 (Thu, 27 Mar 2003) | 5 lines

bug 1685: we should clean PATH when we start if we're in taint mode.
This fixes a Sys::Hostname problem in 5.005, but it's a good idea
anyway since we won't be able to use PATH unless it's cleaned in taint
mode anyway.

