r3791 | climent | 2002-10-27 10:12:16 -0800 (Sun, 27 Oct 2002) | 2 lines

Small change in rule

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r3790 | felicity | 2002-10-27 08:30:33 -0800 (Sun, 27 Oct 2002) | 5 lines

If we're running mass-check against a subset of rules with no bayes,
trying to get the bayes score spews "uninitialized value" at us.
This code fixes that by checking if the score is set.  If it's not,
ignore the bayes output.

